cast silver, raised and chased, from a set of three candelabra;

consisting of one pair of 3 branch and one larger 3-branch, the centre socket of each fitted with a silver eagle with outspread wings, London

The bases of the two smaller examples of elaborate rococo style design incorporating a dolphin, a lion's mask and paws and a chimerical water beast in cartouches separated by foliate scrolls, flowerheads and spiralling up to an eagle entwined about a lion mask at t he centre and then up to a candle socket ornamented with a lion mask, a human mask and flowers. Each fitted with a broad bobeche and socket, similarly hallmarked and bearing an armorial of an upraised armored with sword above a crescent and opposite a crown with four points; into this element fits a two-branched rococo style arm, similarly hallmarked and having candle sockets with flowers, a lion mask and a human head, each socket with further removable bobeches similarly hallmarked. Into the centre of this screws a stylized 4-winged vasiform element, the wings separated by flowerheads, with armorials and hallmarks similar to the above; this element fitted with an additional socket and bobeche, similarly hallmarked and bearing the same armorials. This element fitted with a cast eagle of heavy weight similarly hallmarked but with the date letter "b" for 1817. The largest candelabrum of similar design in the base but rising to two eagles spiralling around a lion mask as the shaft and hallmarked for 1817; the single socket fitted with a 3-branched element of spiral design circulating around a centrl font-like device capped by 3 stylized acanthus leaf groups (hallmarked with a king's head and a lion rampant); each arm fitted with a deep, broad bobeche with an eagle on the underside and a spiral arrangement of water leaves (hallmarked with maker's mark, and lion rampant on underside) each sock with a screw-in shaft and ornamented with flowerheads, a lion mask, and a human mask and in turn fitted with a bobeche and socket hallmarked as on the smaller pair and bearing similar armorials; at centre, above the diadem-like acanthus leaf decoration element, a 4-winged vasiform element as in the smaller pair and ornamented with a king's head, a lion rampant and a partially abraded maker's mark. Into this, a socket and bobeche hallmarked as above and fitted with a similar heavy eagle with out-spread wings.
